From c5c096fb02a65d36fda05f64ac1d159f2588c19e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: patamin-lab <patamin@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 06:59:29 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Replace Supabase Storage with Google Drive for
 photo/video uploads

Per dealer's request: report photos and videos now go to Google Drive
instead of Supabase Storage, organized as {dealer}/{jobId}/ (dealer
short name, then the human job number).

- src/lib/googleDrive.ts (new): service-account auth, per-dealer/job
  folder lookup-or-create, upload + 'anyone with link can view'
  permission, and relocatePendingFiles() to move new-report uploads
  out of a dealer's _pending folder into the real job folder once the
  record (and its job_id) exists
- src/app/api/upload/route.ts: uploads to Drive instead of Supabase
  Storage; accepts dealerId (always) and jobId (when already known)
- src/app/api/records/route.ts: after creating a record, relocates any
  _pending Drive files for that dealer into the new job's folder
- report-form.tsx / update-form.tsx: pass dealerId/jobId through to
  the upload call so files land in the right folder

Requires three new env vars in Vercel + .env.local, not included here
since they're secrets/identifiers only the dealer can supply:
  GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_EMAIL
  GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY
  GOOGLE_DRIVE_ROOT_FOLDER_ID
